@startuml tmf622-service-provisioning

title TMF622 Product Order — Async Provisioning Flow

skinparam sequence {
    ArrowColor #333333
    ActorBorderColor #333333
    LifeLineBorderColor #333333
    ParticipantBorderColor #333333
    ParticipantBackgroundColor #F5F5F5
    BoxBorderColor #999999
    BoxBackgroundColor #FAFAFA
    NoteBackgroundColor #FFFDE7
    NoteBorderColor #F9A825
}

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 6

' ─────────────────────────────────────────
' PARTICIPANTS
' ─────────────────────────────────────────

box "Channel Partner" #EEF2FF
    participant "Partner System\n(CRM / Portal)" as PARTNER
    participant "Partner Webhook\nEndpoint" as WEBHOOK
end box

box "Integration Layer" #F0FFF4
    participant "API Gateway\n(Auth + Rate Limit)" as GW
    participant "Order Manager\n(TMF622)" as OM
end box

box "Backend Systems" #FFF8F0
    participant "Product Catalog\n(TMF620)" as CAT
    participant "BSS / OSS\nFulfillment" as BSS
end box

' ─────────────────────────────────────────
' STEP 1: AUTHENTICATION
' ─────────────────────────────────────────

== Step 1: Authenticate (OAuth 2.0 Client Credentials) ==

PARTNER -> GW : POST /oauth/token\nclient_id + client_secret
GW --> PARTNER : 200 OK\naccess_token (JWT, 1hr TTL)

note right of PARTNER
  Partner caches token.
  Reuses until expiry.
  All subsequent calls
  include Bearer token.
end note

' ─────────────────────────────────────────
' STEP 2: CATALOG LOOKUP
' ─────────────────────────────────────────

== Step 2: Catalog Lookup (TMF620) ==

PARTNER -> GW : GET /productOffering?category=MOBILE_BUSINESS\nAuthorization: Bearer {token}
GW -> CAT : validate token\nroute request
CAT --> GW : 200 OK — productOffering list\n[{id, name, price, characteristics}]
GW --> PARTNER : 200 OK — productOffering list

note right of PARTNER
  Partner selects the
  offering to order.
  Stores offering ID
  for the order request.
end note

' ─────────────────────────────────────────
' STEP 3: SUBMIT ORDER
' ─────────────────────────────────────────

== Step 3: Submit Product Order (TMF622) ==

PARTNER -> GW : POST /productOrder\nIdempotency-Key: {uuid}\nAuthorization: Bearer {token}\n\nbody: {\n  productOffering.id,\n  account.id,\n  orderItem characteristics,\n  relatedParty (end user)\n}

GW -> OM : validate token + rate limit\nforward order

OM -> CAT : validate offering ID\ncheck account eligibility
CAT --> OM : offering valid\naccount ACTIVE, under limit

OM --> GW : 202 Accepted\n{\n  id: "PO-20260525-001",\n  state: "ACKNOWLEDGED",\n  statusUrl: "/productOrder/PO-20260525-001"\n}
GW --> PARTNER : 202 Accepted\ncorrelationId + statusUrl

note right of PARTNER
  Partner stores correlationId.
  Does NOT wait — continues
  other work. Will receive
  webhook when done.
end note

' ─────────────────────────────────────────
' STEP 4: ASYNC FULFILLMENT
' ─────────────────────────────────────────

== Step 4: Async Fulfillment (BSS/OSS) ==

OM -> BSS : submit service order\n(TMF641 Service Order)
OM --> PARTNER : (no response — async)

note over BSS
  BSS provisions the service:
  SIM activation, plan assignment,
  network configuration.
  Duration: 60–120 seconds typical.
end note

BSS -> BSS : provision service\n[INPROGRESS]

' ─────────────────────────────────────────
' STEP 5: OPTIONAL POLLING
' ─────────────────────────────────────────

== Step 5: Optional — Partner Polls for Status ==

PARTNER -> GW : GET /productOrder/PO-20260525-001\nAuthorization: Bearer {token}
GW -> OM : route
OM --> GW : 200 OK\n{ state: "INPROGRESS" }
GW --> PARTNER : 200 OK\n{ state: "INPROGRESS" }

note right of PARTNER
  Polling is the FALLBACK.
  Use webhooks where possible.
  Some partners poll due to
  firewall restrictions on
  inbound HTTPS.
end note

' ─────────────────────────────────────────
' STEP 6: FULFILLMENT COMPLETE → WEBHOOK
' ─────────────────────────────────────────

== Step 6: Fulfillment Complete — Webhook Callback ==

BSS --> OM : provisioning complete\nserviceId, identifier assigned
OM -> OM : update order state\n→ COMPLETED

OM -> WEBHOOK : POST https://partner.com/webhooks/carrier\nX-Signature: HMAC-SHA256\n\n{\n  correlationId: "PO-20260525-001",\n  event: "PRODUCT_ORDER_COMPLETED",\n  state: "COMPLETED",\n  orderItem: {\n    serviceId: "SVC-9876",\n    identifier: "+13125551234"\n  }\n}

WEBHOOK --> OM : 200 OK (ACK within 5s)

note right of WEBHOOK
  Partner MUST respond 200
  within 5 seconds.
  Retry policy: 3 attempts,
  exponential backoff
  (30s → 60s → 120s).
  Payload verified with
  HMAC-SHA256 signature.
end note

' ─────────────────────────────────────────
' STEP 7: FAILURE PATH
' ─────────────────────────────────────────

== Step 7: Failure Path (alternate) ==

BSS --> OM : provisioning failed\nerrorCode: IMEI_BLOCKED
OM -> OM : update order state\n→ FAILED

OM -> WEBHOOK : POST https://partner.com/webhooks/carrier\n{\n  correlationId: "PO-20260525-001",\n  event: "PRODUCT_ORDER_FAILED",\n  state: "FAILED",\n  error: {\n    code: "IMEI_BLOCKED",\n    message: "Device not eligible for activation"\n  }\n}

WEBHOOK --> OM : 200 OK (ACK)

note right of WEBHOOK
  Partner receives failure
  event with machine-readable
  error code. Can retry with
  a new Idempotency-Key if
  the issue is resolved.
end note

@enduml
